tle=The Thanksgiving Treasure (1973 TV Movie) Filming & Production |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0228392/locations?ref_=tt_dt_dt |website=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=24 November 2018}}</ref>\n* Parts of the 1996 film ''[[Fly Away Home]]'' were filmed in Scugog.\n* The downtown scenes from 2004's ''[[Welcome to Mooseport]]'' were shot in Port Perry.\n* The downtown scenes from ''[[Hemlock Grove (TV series)|Hemlock Grove]]'' were shot in Port Perry.\n* In Season 3 \"Lakeside\" of ''[[American Gods (TV series)]]'' some parts were shot in downtown Port Perry. They painted the mill black and made other little changes around the town\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of townships in Ontario]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikinews2|Canadian union upset over Scugog councilor lowering flag|Scugog flag controversy comes to an end}}\n* {{Commons category-inline}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051001030441/http://www.township.scugog.on.ca/ Township of Scugog]\n* [ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/canmatrix2/50k_pdf/031/d/ Downloadable 1:50 000 topographical map of Scugog (map 31D02)]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, by the [[Natural Resources Canada|Ministry of Natural Resources]]\n\n{{Geographic location|\nCenter=Scugog<br>{{nobold|(surrounds [[Mississaugas of Scugog Island First Nation|Mississaugas of Scugog Island]])}}|\nNorth=[[Brock, Ontario|Brock]]|\nWest=[[Uxbridge, Ontario|Uxbridge]]|\nEast=[[Kawartha Lakes, Ontario|Kawartha Lakes]]|\nSouth=[[Whitby, Ontario|Whitby]], [[Oshawa]], [[Clarington, Ontario|Clarington]]}}\n\n{{Durham region}}\n{{Greater Toronto Area}}\n\n[[Category:Township municipalities in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Lower-tier municipalities in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Municipalities in Durham Region]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See Template:Infobox Settlement for additional fields that may be available-->\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-