y Home]]'' were filmed in Scugog.\n* The downtown scenes from 2004's ''[[Welcome to Mooseport]]'' were shot in Port Perry.\n* The downtown scenes from ''[[Hemlock Grove (TV series)|Hemlock Grove]]'' were shot in Port Perry.\n* In Season 3 \"Lakeside\" of ''[[American Gods (TV series)]]'' some parts were shot in downtown Port Perry. They painted the mill black and made other little changes around the town\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of townships in Ontario]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikinews2|Canadian union upset over Scugog councilor lowering flag|Scugog flag controversy comes to an end}}\n* {{Commons category-inline}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051001030441/http://www.township.scugog.on.ca/ Township of Scugog]\n* [ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/canmatrix2/50k_pdf/031/d/ Downloadable 1:50 000 topographical map of Scugog (map 31D02)]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, by the [[Natural Resources Canada|Ministry of Natural Resources]]\n\n{{Geographic location|\nCenter=Scugog<br>{{nobold|(surrounds [[Mississaugas of Scugog Island First Nation|Mississaugas of Scugog Island]])}}|\nNorth=[[Brock, Ontario|Brock]]|\nWest=[[Uxbridge, Ontario|Uxbridge]]|\nEast=[[Kawartha Lakes, Ontario|Kawartha Lakes]]|\nSouth=[[Whitby, Ontario|Whitby]], [[Oshawa]], [[Clarington, Ontario|Clarington]]}}\n\n{{Durham region}}\n{{Greater Toronto Area}}\n\n[[Category:Township municipalities in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Lower-tier municipalities in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Municipalities in Durham Region]]\n", "name_user": "Bellowhead678", "label": "safe", "comment": "Deobrah->Deborah -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scugog"}
{"title_page": "1997 Davis Cup World Group", "text_new": "{{Infobox tennis tournament year|1997|Davis Cup World Group\n| date=7 February \u2013 30 November\n| edition=17th\n| champ={{davis-big|SWE}}\n| main_name=Davis Cup\n}}\n\n{{main|1997 Davis Cup}}\n\nThe '''World Group''' was the highest level of [[Davis Cup]] competition in 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.daviscup.com/en/draws-results/world-group.aspx#/1997|title=World Group 1997|publisher=DavisCup.com|accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref> The first-round losers went into the [[1997 Davis Cup World Group Qualifying Round|Davis Cup World Group Qualifying Round]], and the winners progressed to the quarterfinals and were guaranteed a World Group spot for [[1998 Davis Cup World Group|1998]].\n\n[[France Davis Cup team|France]] were the defending champions, but were eliminated in the first round.\n\n[[Sweden Davis Cup team|Sweden]] won the title, defeating the [[United States Davis Cup team|United States]] in the final, 5\u20130. The final was held at the [[Scandinavium]] in [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]], from 28 to 30 November.<ref name=\"WG Final\" /> It was the Swedish team's 6th Davis Cup title overall.\n\n==Participating teams==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:98%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=4|Participating teams\n|-\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|AUS}}\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|BRA}}\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|CZE}}\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|FRA}}\n|-\n!{{Davis-big|GER}}\n!{{Davis-big|IND}}\n!{{Davis-big|ITA}}\n!{{Davis-big|MEX}}\n|-\n!{{Davis-big|NED}}\n!{{Davis-big|ROU}}\n!{{Davis-big|RUS}}\n!{{Davis-big|RSA}}\n|-\n!{{Davis-big|ESP}}\n!{{Davis-big|SWE}}\n!{{Davis-big|SUI}}\n!{{Davis-big|USA}}\n|}\n\n==Draw==\n{{DCWorld\n| RD1-date=7\u20139 February\n| RD2-date=4\u20136 April\n| RD3-date=19\u201321 September\n| RD4-date=28\u201330 November\n\n| RD1T1-loc=[[Ribeir\u00e3o Preto]], [[Brazil]] (clay)\n| RD1-seed1= | RD1-team1={{Davis|USA}} | RD1-score1=4\n| RD1-seed2= | RD1-team2={{Davis|BRA}} | RD1-score2=1\n\n| RD1T2-loc=[[Bucharest]], [[Romania]] (indoor hard)\n| RD1-seed3= | RD1-team3={{Davis|NED}} | RD1-score3=3\n| RD1-seed4= | RD1-team4={{Davis|ROU}} | RD1-score4=2\n\n| RD1T3-loc=[[Sydney]], [[Australia]] (grass)\n| RD1-seed5= | RD1-team5={{Davis|FRA}} | RD1-score5=1\n| RD1-seed6= | RD1-team6={{Davis|AUS}} | RD1-score6=4\n\n| RD1T4-loc=[[P\u0159\u00edbram]], [[Czech Republic]] (indoor clay)\n| RD1-seed7= | RD1-team7={{Davis|CZE}} | RD1-score7=3\n| RD1-seed8= | RD1-team8={{Davis|IND}} | RD1-score8=2\n\n| RD1T5-loc=[[Rome]], [[Italy]] (clay)\n| RD1-seed9= | RD1-team9={{Davis|MEX}} | RD1-score9=1\n| RD1-seed10= | RD1-team10={{Davis|ITA}} | RD1-score10=4\n\n| RD1T6-loc=[[Mallorca]], [[Spain]] (clay)\n| RD1-seed11= | RD1-team11={{Davis|ESP}} | RD1-score11=4\n| RD1-seed12= | RD1-team12={{Davis|GER}} | RD1-score12=1\n\n| RD1T7-loc=[[Durban]], [[South Africa]] (hard)\n| RD1-seed13= | RD1-team13={{Davis|RSA}} | RD1-score13=3\n| RD1-seed14= | RD1-team14={{Davis|RUS}} | RD1-score14=1\n\n| RD1T8-loc=[[Lule\u00e5]], [[Sweden]] (indoor hard)\n| RD1-seed15= | RD1-team15={{Davis|SUI}} | RD1-score15=1\n| RD1-seed16= | RD1-team16={{Davis|SWE}} | RD1-score16=4\n\n| RD2T1-loc=[[Newport Beach, California|Newport Beach, CA]], [[United States]] (hard)\n| RD2-seed1= | RD2-team1={{Davis|USA}} | RD2-score1=4\n| RD2-seed2= | RD2-team2={{Davis|NED}} | RD2-score2=1\n\n| RD2T2-loc=[[Adelaide]], [[Australia]] (grass)\n| RD2-seed3= | RD2-team3={{Davis|AUS}} | RD2-score3=5\n| RD2-seed4= | RD2-team4={{Davis|CZE}} | RD2-score4=0\n\n| RD2T3-loc=[[Pesaro]], [[Italy]] (indoor carpet)\n| RD2-seed5= | RD2-team5={{Davis|ITA}} | RD2-score5=4\n| RD2-seed6= | RD2-team6={{Davis|ESP}} | RD2-score6=1\n\n| RD2T4-loc=[[V\u00e4xj\u00f6]], [[Sweden]] (indoor carpet)\n| RD2-seed7= | RD2-team7={{Davis|RSA}} | RD2-score7=2\n| RD2-seed8= | RD2-team8={{Davis|SWE}} | RD2-score8=3\n\n| RD3T1-loc=[[Washington, D.C.|Washington, DC]], [[United States]] (hard)\n| RD3-seed1= | RD3-team1={{Davis|USA}} | RD3-score1=4\n| RD3-seed2= | RD3-team2={{Davi