guaranteed a World Group spot for [[1998 Davis Cup World Group|1998]].\n\n[[France Davis Cup team|France]] were the defending champions, but were eliminated in the first round.\n\n[[Sweden Davis Cup team|Sweden]] won the title, defeating the [[United States Davis Cup team|United States]] in the final, 5\u20130. The final was held at the [[Scandinavium]] in [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]], from 28 to 30 November.<ref name=\"WG Final\" /> It was the Swedish team's 6th Davis Cup title overall.\n\n==Participating teams==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:98%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=4|Participating teams\n|-\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|AUS}}\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|BRA}}\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|CZE}}\n!width=25%|{{Davis-big|FRA}}\n|-\n!{{Davis-big|GER}}\n!{{Davis-big|IND}}\n!{{Davis-big|ITA}}\n!{{Davis-big|MEX}}\n|-\n!{{Davis-big|NED}}\n!{{Davis-big|ROU}}\n!{{Davis-big|RUS}}\n!{{Davis-big|RSA}}\n|-\n!{{Davis-big|ESP}}\n!{{Davis-big|SWE}}\n!{{Davis-big|SUI}}\n!{{Davis-big|USA}}\n|}\n\n==Draw==\n{{DCWorld\n| RD1-date=7\u20139 February\n| RD2-date=4\u20136 April\n| RD3-date=19\u201321 September\n| RD4-date=28\u201330 November\n\n| RD1T1-loc=[[Ribeir\u00e3o Preto]], [[Brazil]] (clay)\n| RD1-seed1= | RD1-team1={{Davis|USA}} | RD1-score1=4\n| RD1-seed2= | RD1-team2={{Davis|BRA}} | RD1-score2=1\n\n| RD1T2-loc=[[Bucharest]], [[Romania]] (indoor hard)\n| RD1-seed3= | RD1-team3={{Davis|NED}} | RD1-score3=3\n| RD1-seed4= | RD1-team4={{Davis|ROU}} | RD1-score4=2\n\n| RD1T3-loc=[[Sydney]], [[Australia]] (grass)\n| RD1-seed5= | RD1-team5={{Davis|FRA}} | RD1-score5=1\n| RD1-seed6= | RD1-team6={{Davis|AUS}} | RD1-score6=4\n\n| RD1T4-loc=[[P\u0159\u00edbram]], [[Czech Republic]] (indoor clay)\n| RD1-seed7= | RD1-team7={{Davis|CZE}} | RD1-score7=3\n| RD1-seed8= | RD1-team8={{Davis|IND}} | RD1-score8=2\n\n| RD1T5-loc=[[Rome]], [[Italy]] (clay)\n| RD1-seed9= | RD1-team9={{Davis|MEX}} | RD1-score9=1\n| RD1-seed10= | RD1-team10={{Davis|ITA}} | RD1-score10=4\n\n| RD1T6-loc=[[Mallorca]], [[Spain]] (clay)\n